CHOLERA - PHILIPPINES (02)
**************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Cholera - Philippines 980421230614
Date: Wed, 22 Apr 1998 06:58:20 +0000
From: Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background data on cholera in the Philippines were extracted
from the GIDEON software program:
The following are listed as 'Infected Areas' by the World Health
Organization: National Capital Region, Regions 4 to 9 and Regions 11 and 12.
National reporting data as follows:
Year Cases Deaths
1991 864
1992 345
1993 708 10
1994 3,340 27
1995 847 4
1996 * 1,402 14
No cases were officially reported in 1997
*including 284 suspect cases (5 fatal) from Paco and San Andres (Manila)
during September 1996
--
Dr. Steve Berger
e-mail: mberger@post.tau.ac.il
